.TH "suspend_valid_only_mem" 9 "suspend_valid_only_mem" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
suspend_valid_only_mem \- Generic memory-only valid callback.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" suspend_valid_only_mem
.BI "(suspend_state_t state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
Target system sleep state.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Platform drivers that implement mem suspend only and only need to check for
that in their .\fBvalid\fP callback can use this instead of rolling their own
\&.\fBvalid\fP callback.
